						               													<description>In this little card game you are trying to capture magical creature named Lirog. This old and powerfull but not too smart being, has something priceless in his posession. As one of the wizards you are trying to lure him into the trap using spells and forest fruits. In the deck there are 12 kind of cards with distiguish powers. Every player is trying to program the game area, so that after activation, Lirog will enter their trap.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are only 52 cards in the deck. At the start of the game players recive 3 random cards each. In a specified order they can  put one card on the game board and take 1 card from the market or take 2 cards from the market. After all players finished their turns, creature will make his moves. Depending on  cards that affect him, he will move  around the game board. If during move phase Lirog enters one of the traps, the game ends. Owner of that trap becomes the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
